{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5a14b82f-a5f4-4c16-8faa-20a03b6352d8","content":"In your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events on the returned `Window`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Activated     += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated   += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Resumed       += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Destroying    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Typical transition order:**\n\n| Action | Events fired |\n|---|---|\n| App launch | `Created → Activated` |\n| User switches away | `Deactivated → Stopped` |\n| User returns | `Resumed → Activated` |\n| App closed | `Deactivated → Stopped → Destroying` |\n| iOS background save | `Backgrounding` (use `e.State` to persist data) |\n\n> **Note:** `Backgrounding` is iOS-only. `Resumed`/`Stopped` map to platform concepts like `onPause`/`onResume` (Android) and `OnResignActivation`/`DidEnterBackground` (iOS).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c33d6fb9-a68d-46b8-a81b-e1527ade1fbe","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI Window lifecycle events and how to subscribe to them for logging/debugging. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI — I can answer directly without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":462,"requestId":"B7CD:28DDBA:137AD5:19829E:69FFD7FE"},"id":"d30cf092-82c7-401f-ac43-a2c896515651","timestamp":"2026-05-10T00:57:42.602Z","parentId":"9e6115e8-06ad-48fb-8d88-847e3dddd548"}
